{
  "texts": [
    "DNN variants without the early-exit branch have steady execution latency and, thus, have only one density area centred around a very narrow range.",
    "On the other hand, DNN variants with the early-exit branch have two density areas displaying the latency timings of requests exiting at two exit branches.",
    "The median latency is higher for smaller DNNs or smaller batch sizes because of the extra time required to execute the additional exit branch.",
    "For bigger DNNs and larger batch sizes, the median execution latency of the early-exit DNN variant is lower than that without early-exit.",
    "This is because bigger DNNs have higher exit probabilities, and thus more requests exit at the first branch, causing a significant reduction in the overall batch inference time."
  ]
}